# Skill: Design System Upgrade

Use this skill when working on colors, typography, spacing, shadows, borders, cards, badges, buttons, visual hierarchy, or responsive layout foundations.

## Objective
Extend the existing design-token system instead of hardcoding scattered styles.

## Rules
- Prefer CSS custom properties in `styles/tokens.css` for reusable values.
- Keep maroon as the primary editorial brand color.
- Add colors for premium surfaces, soft backgrounds, overlays, focus rings, muted text, and section blocks.
- Use restrained shadows; this is an editorial news portal, not a SaaS dashboard.
- Keep radii refined and professional.
- Tune Bangla typography carefully: line-height should not feel cramped.
- Use English typography only as a secondary mode.

## Recommended Token Groups
- Brand colors
- Surface/background colors
- Text/ink colors
- Border/rule colors
- Shadow/elevation
- Radius
- Spacing
- Layout/container
- Motion/easing
- Focus states

## Acceptance Checklist
- Tokens are clearly named.
- New tokens are commented by group.
- Styles reuse tokens instead of repeated raw values.
- Bangla and English modes both remain visually balanced.
